## Better Sound on ZenOS

We've completely rewritten the audio module (`zenos.audio`) to leverage the latest PipeWire features. This update brings low-latency monitoring by default and a new system-wide equalizer interface.

### New Features

* **Auto-Routing:** Headphones are now prioritized automatically when plugged in.
* **Equalizer:** Added `zenos.audio.equalizer.presets` for bass boost and vocal clarity.
* **Bluetooth:** LDAC codec support is now enabled out-of-the-box.

### Migration

If you were using PulseAudio manually, please remove `services.pulseaudio.enable` from your config.

```nix
zenos.audio = {
  enable = true;
  lowLatency = true;
  equalizer.preset = "bass-boost";
};
```
